Java Naming Convensions
-------------------------

1. Class
----------
-> Every class should be start with Upper case letter.
-> If there are more than one word in the class, then
   starting letter of each new word should be capitalized.
Ex: Employee, System, SalariedEmployee,DataInputStream 

2. Methods, variable, objects
--------------------------------
-> should start with lowercase letter. 
-> If there are more than one word, then, each word
   first letter should be capitalized
Ex: age, studentName, processEmployeeSalary()

3. key words, packages
----------------------
-> all should be in lower case only
Ex: int, class, java.lang

4. const
---------
-> all const should be in upoper case letters
Ex: PI, MAX_AGE, FONT_NAME